=== 教育 ===
1942年，英軍投降後，為推廣日語，日軍開辦昭南日本学園。[[阮斐娜|阮斐娜]]在她的著作《帝國的太陽下：日本的台灣及南方殖民地文學》中提到日軍在東南亞的日語推廣，新加坡最為成功<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CFEyQWoNSJ8C&pg=PA43|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|date=2003-09-30|isbn=978-0-8248-2592-8|language=en|first=Faye Yuan|last=Kleeman|title=Under an Imperial Sun: Japanese Colonial Literature of Taiwan and the South|pages=43|quote=The most successful was the Japanese school in Singapore. A month after the British surrendered (February 15, 1942), Japan renamed the island Shonan (literally "illuminating the south") and founded the famous Shonan Japanese School (Shōnan Nihon Gakuen 昭南日本学園)|access-date=2022-02-15|archive-date=2021-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411201121/https://books.google.com/books?id=CFEyQWoNSJ8C&pg=PA43}}</ref>。此外，日軍亦設立「昭南第一日本人學校」<ref>{{Cite web|title=シンガポール日本人学校-A BRIEF HISTORY|url=http://www.sjs.edu.sg/english/office_304.html|archive-url=https://archive.is/20140102074840/http://www.sjs.edu.sg/english/office_304.html#selection-59.0-59.12|archive-date=2014-01-02|access-date=2021-10-30|dead-url=yes}}</ref>({{Lang-ja|昭南第一日本人学校}}，今新加坡日僑學校<ref>{{Cite web|title=シンガポール日本人学校 - The Japanese School Singapore|url=https://www.sjs.edu.sg/|access-date=2021-10-30|work=www.sjs.edu.sg|archive-date=2021-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211030183137/https://www.sjs.edu.sg/|dead-url=no}}</ref>)。

1943年7月1日起，日軍為加強日語普及，禁止英語的各類通信，包含明信片與書信。僅有學務用書和軍方認可的書可以使用英文。<ref>英語通信禁止，台灣日日新報，1943年1月15日</ref>

